(e) issue guidelines, ad visories, vulnerability notes and white papers relating to information 
security practices, procedures, preventation, response and reporting of cyber incidents; 
(f) such other functions relating to cyber security as may be prescribed. 
(5) The manner of perf orming functions and duties of the agency referred to in sub -section (1) shall 
be such as may be prescribed. 
(6) For carrying out the provisions of sub -section (4), the agency referred to in sub -section (1) may 
call for information and give direction to th e service providers, intermediaries, data centres, body 
corporate and any other person. 
